rht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Baron Robert Monhout was born in 1163, in Chester, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Nichole de Rising. He died in 1229, at the age of 66."},"et":{"1163–1229":"1163–1229","1175–1231":"1175–1231","1182–1245":"1182–1245","1245":"1245","1231":"1231","1175":"1175","1163":"1163","1182":"1182","1229":"1229","Chester,Cheshire,England.":"Chester, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1163–1229":"1163–1229","1175–1231":"1175–1231","1182–1245":"1182–1245","1245":"1245","1231":"1231","1175":"1175","1163":"1163","1182":"1182","1229":"1229","Chester,Cheshire,England.":"Chester, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1163–1229":"1163–1229","1175–1231":"1175–1231","1182–1245":"1182–1245","1245":"1245","1231":"1231","1175":"1175","1163":"1163","1182":"1182","1229":"1229","Chester,Cheshire,England.":"Chester, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Baron Robert Monhout est né en 1163, à Chester, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Nichole de Rising. Il est décédé en 1229, à l’âge de 66 ans."},"de":{"1163–1229":"1163–1229","1175–1231":"1175–1231","1182–1245":"1182–1245","1245":"1245","1231":"1231","1175":"1175","1163":"1163","1182":"1182","1229":"1229","C